[2] Japan (Tottori): wild duck
Date: Thu 27 Nov 2014
Source: Sputnik News [edited]
http://sputniknews.com/asia/20141127/1015219131.html


A highly pathogenic avian influenza type H5N8 was discovered in the southwestern Tottori Prefecture in Japan, Kyodo news agency reported [Thu 27 Nov 2014].

The virus was detected in the analysis of duck fecal samples taken on 18 Nov 2014, according to the agency.

Japan's Ministry of the Environment has established a 10-km (6-mile) monitoring zone in the region, where the virus was detected. It is yet
unknown if the government is planning to test wild birds for the disease, according to Kyodo.

[Byline: A Kornyushenko)

